SIMPLE: resolute
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Resolute
<hw>Res"o*lute</hw> <pr>(r?z"?-l?t)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧solu</ets>. The L. <ets>resolutus</ets> (p. p. of
<ets>resolvere</ets>) means, relaxed, enervated, effeminate. See
<er>Resolve</er>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having a
decided purpose; determined; resolved; fixed in a determination; hence,
bold; firm; steady.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Edward is at hand,⟦br⟧
Ready to fight; therefore be <qex>resolute</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Convinced; satisfied; sure.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Resolving, or explaining; <as>as, the
<ex>Resolute</ex> Doctor Durand</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Determined; decided; fixed; steadfast; steady;
constant; persevering; firm; bold; unshaken.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resolute</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Resolute
<hw>Res"o*lute</hw> <pr>(r?z"?-l?t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who is resolute; hence, a desperado.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Redelivery; repayment.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧Yearly <xex>resolutes</xex>, deductions, and payments.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Bp. Burnet.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resolutely</ent>⟦br⟧
